The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa  today. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from the last close.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index rose for a second day,
gaining 216.82, or 0.7 percent, to 30,897.05 at the 5 p.m. close
in Johannesburg.  Beige Holdings Ltd. (BEG)  : The pharmaceutical and
cosmetic manufacturer publishes earnings for the year to March
31. The stock was unchanged at 4 cents.  Hyprop Investments Ltd. (HYP)  : The property investment
company holds its annual general meeting. The shares lost 1
cent, or less than 0.1 percent, to 54 rand.  Omnia Holdings Ltd. (OMN)  : The distributor of
fertilizers and explosives reports earnings for the year ended
March 31.  The stock fell 1.74 rand, or 2.3 percent, to 74.52
rand.  Vunani Ltd. (VUN)  : The financial-services company said
in a regulatory statement after the market closed itâ€™s made
progress in restructuring its property investments into one
vehicle, VPIF, which is preparing for a listing on the main
board of the JSE Ltd. The shares were unchanged at 6 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
